text:
Johnson Street, west from No. 67 at right foreground. In the background are the U. S. Post Office building, and the "Elevated" station of the Myrtle Ave., Line of the B.M.T. June 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
title: Brooklyn: Johnson Street

text:
Johnson Street, north side, from Jay to Pearl Streets, showing the rear of a row of very old frame and brick dwellings fronting on the aforementioned side of the thoroughfare. The view is southwestward from Jay Street. In the background is the Montague Court Building.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: April 3, 1936
View 2: August 23, 1939
View 3: Sept. 6, 1939

View 4: Johnson Street, seen from Duffield St.
View 5: N.W. Corner Johnson St. and Fleet Place.
